I was just informed through the national notary association and blue =
notary that documents that are out of state can not be notarized.=20
My deepest apologies for the inconvenience and I=E2=80=99ve included the =
information I received from the representative below.

My Best regards and sincere apologies,

~Evan McCall


Yes, a Florida notary can notarize a document from another state, but =
the notarization must occur within the state of Florida and adhere to =
Florida's notary laws. The document's origin state is irrelevant as long =
as the notarization itself complies with Florida's regulations.=20
Florida Notary Authority:
Florida notaries are authorized to perform notarial acts within the =
geographical boundaries of Florida.=20

Out-of-State Documents:
A Florida notary can notarize a document that was created in another =
state, as long as the notarization takes place within Florida.=20

Compliance with Florida Law:
The notarization process must follow all applicable Florida notary laws =
and regulations, including proper identification of the signer, =
completion of the notarial certificate, and any other relevant =
procedures.=20

Venue:
If the document has a pre-printed notarial certificate with a different =
venue (state and county), the notary must cross it out and insert the =
correct Florida venue.=20

No Out-of-State Notarizations:
A Florida notary cannot perform notarizations outside of Florida's =
borders, even if the document is related to another state.=20

